Japanese personal savings grew 10.3 pctin 1986 from 1985 helped by a sharp increase in stockinvestments by individuals, the Bank of Japan said.    Outstanding savings on December 31, 1986 totalled 545,303billion yen. Funds in investment trusts alone totalled 21,918billion yen, up 37.4 pct from a year earlier.    The outstanding balance also included deposits at banks andpost offices, up 7.4 pct to 337,867 billion yen, savings in theform of insurance, up 18.6 pct to 111,431 billion, corporatebond investments, up 7.8 pct to 46,867 billion, and investmentsin trust banks, up 4.1 pct to 27,220 billion. REUTER&#3;